==English==

===Etymology===
Shortened from "twenty-four hours a day, seven days a week."

===Alternative spellings===
'''24/7'''

===Adverb===
'''twenty-four seven'''

# {{colloquial}} Constantly, without interruption.
#:''They're open twenty-four seven, you can go there any time you want.''
# An [[w:abbreviation|abbreviation]] which stands for "24 hours a day, 7 days a week", including holidays and days otherwise that may alter limitations of work.  In [[w:commerce|commerce]] and [[w:industry|industry]], it identifies a round-the-clock service, as might be offered by a [[w:supermarket|supermarket]], [[w:ATM|ATM]], [[w:Filling station|gas station]], [[w:concierge|concierge]] service or manned datacenter.

